rnor Republican Primary Election Runoff, 2019\n|-\n|'''Party'''\n|'''Candidate'''\n|'''Votes'''\n|'''%'''\n|-\n|Republican\n|'''Tate Reeves'''\n|176,251\n|54.28\n|-\n|Republican\n|Bill Waller Jr.\n|148,471\n|45.72\n|}\n\n{{Election box begin|\n| title = Mississippi gubernatorial election, 2019<ref>{{cite web|url=https://data.clarionledger.com/mississippi-general-election-results-2019/ |title=Mississippi General Election Results 2019 |publisher=ClarionLedger.com |date=2019-11-05 |accessdate=2019-11-06}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link \n| candidate = [[Tate Reeves]]\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = 443,063\n| percentage = 52.26\n| change = -14.12%\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link\n| candidate = [[Jim Hood]]\n| party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| votes = 394,177\n| percentage = 46.49\n| change = +14.24%\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link\n| candidate = David Singletary\n| party = Independent (United States)\n| votes = 8,145\n| percentage = 0.96\n| change = N/A\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link \n| candidate = Bob Hickingbottom\n| party = Constitution Party (United States)\n| votes = 2,495\n| percentage = 0.29\n| change = N/A\n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes = 847,880\n| percentage = 100%\n| change = N/A\n}}\n{{Election box hold with party link no swing\n  |winner     = Republican Party (United States)\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category-inline}}\n* [https://www.tatereeves.com/ Official website]\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=Peyton Prospere}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Mississippi State Treasurer|Treasurer of Mississippi]]|years=2004\u20132012}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Lynn Fitch]]}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|rows=2|before=[[Phil Bryant]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title={{nowrap|[[List of lieutenant governors of Mississippi|Lieutenant Governor of Mississippi]]}}|years=2012\u20132020}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Delbert Hosemann]]}}\n|-\n{{s-ttl|