ississippi]]\n", "name_user": "AlsoWukai", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eControversy", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tate_Reeves"}
{"title_page": "All My Love (Major Lazer song)", "text_new": "{{good article}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name     = All My Love\n| cover    = ML AG AML.jpg\n| alt      = An animated image of a man with armor kneeling down while surrounded in a pile of metal scraps. A yellow spotlight appears along a black and light pink background.\n| caption  = Artwork released by Major Lazer\n| type     = song\n| artist   = [[Major Lazer]] featuring [[Ariana Grande]]\n| album    = [[The Hunger Games: Mockingjay, Part 1 (soundtrack)|The Hunger Games:<br>Mockingjay, Part 1]]\n| released = {{Start date|2014|11|13|df=yes}}\n| format   = [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| recorded =\n| studio   =\n| venue    =\n| genre    = {{hlist|[[Dancehall]]|[[electropop]]}}\n| length   = {{Duration|m=3|s=32}}\n| label    = [[Republic Records|Republic]]\n| writer   = {{hlist|[[Lorde|Ella Yelich-O'Connor]]|[[Ariana Grande|Ariana Grande-Butera]]|[[M\u00d8|Karen \u00d8rsted]]|[[Diplo|Thomas Pentz]]|[[Boaz van de Beatz|Boaz de Jong]]|[[Jr Blender|Philip Meckseper]]}}\n| producer = {{hlist|[[Diplo]]|[[Boaz van de Beatz]]|[[Jr Blender]]}}\n| tracks   = {{The Hunger Games: Mockingjay, Part 1 track listing}}\n}}\n\n\"'''All My Love'''\" is a song by American electronic music project [[Major Lazer]] featuring vocals from American singer [[Ariana Grande]]. It was released on 13 November 2014 as the fifth song from the [[The Hunger Games: Mockingjay, Part 1 (soundtrack)|soundtrack]] for ''[[The Hunger Games: Mockingjay, Part 1]]'' (2014) by [[Republic Records]]. The song was written by Grande, [[Lorde|Ella Yelich-O'Connor]], and [[M\u00d8|Karen \u00d8rsted]] with production handled by [[Boaz van de Beatz]], Jr Blender and [[Diplo]], a member of Major Lazer. It is an [[electropop]] song with elements of [[dancehall]]. It received positive reviews from [[music journalism|music critics]] who complimented the track's production.\n\nCommercially, the track performed modestly in Belgium and charted in France and the United Kingdom. A remix of the song featuring vocals from Grande and soca singer [[Machel Montano]] was released on 21 January 2015 and appears as the final track on Major Lazer's third studio album ''[[Peace Is the Mission]]'' (2015). It features an interpolation of [[Aqua (band)|Aqua]]'s 1997 song \"[[Lollipop (Candyman)]]\". This version performed modestly in Belgium and charted in Canada, peaking at 15 and 87, respectively.\n\n==Background and release==\n[[File:Dangerous Woman Tour in Manchester4 (cropped).jpg|left|thumb|upright|alt=An zoomed-in image of a woman dressed in a white crop top, pants and a jacket performing on stage.|[[Ariana Grande]] co-wrote and contributed vocals to \"All My Love\"]]\n\"All My Love\" was written by [[Lorde]] (credited under her birth-name Ella Yelich-O'Connor), [[Ariana Grande]] and [[M\u00d8|Karen \u00d8rsted]],<ref name=linernotes>{{cite AV media notes|others=Lorde|title=The Hunger Games: Mockingjay \u2013 Part 1|year=2014|publisher=Republic Records}}</ref> while production of the song was handled by Boaz van de Beatz, Jr Blender and [[Diplo]], a member of [[Major Lazer]]. Leaked on 13 November 2014 before the official release date,<ref name=\"spin\"/> \"All My Love\" was included as the fifth track for the [[The Hunger Games: Mockingjay, Part 1 (soundtrack)|soundtrack album]] of the 2014 film ''[[The Hunger Games: Mockingjay \u2013 Part 1|The Hunger Games: Mockingjay, Part 1]]''.<ref name=linernotes/>\n\nLorde's desire to include \"All My Love\" on the film's soundtrack led Diplo to rush the production process of the song. In an annotation posted to [[Genius (website)|Genius]] that Diplo wrote, he mentioned that he was on vacation in London at the same time Grande was there. He managed to communicate with her and go \"back and forth with certain mixes.\" Diplo said that he was willing to \"screw around\" and surprise people with \"this kind of collaboration.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Major Lazer \u2014 All My Love Lyrics|url=https://genius.com/8506300|website=Genius|accessdate=18 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nDiplo first mentioned the track on 16 October 2014 via [[Twitter]]. However, he deleted the tweet afterwards.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Wass |first1=Mike |title=Diplo Reveals Looming Ariana Grande And Major Lazer Collaboration, Possibly Called \u201cAll My Love\u201d |url=http://www.idolator.com/7566836/ariana-grande-diplo-major-lazer-all-my-love-collaboration |accessdate=30 August 2018 |work=Idolator |date=16 October 2014}}</ref> When the album's official track list was announced on 21 October 2014, the song was listed as \"Track 5\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1970037/kanye-haim-pusha-t-charlie-xcx-mockingjay-soundtrack/|title=Lorde's 'Mockingjay' Soundtrack Features Kanye, Haim, Pusha T And Charli XCX|publisher=[[MTV]]|date=October 21, 2014|accessdate=November 18, 2014}}</ref> Lorde, who curated the film's soundtrack, said on Twitter that the song was not excluded for \"secrecy's sake\" but because it was \"not quite finished\".<ref name=\"MTVHungerGames\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1979171/ariana-grande-hunger-games-mockingjay-soundtrack/|title=Is Ariana Grande Behind That Secret 'Hunger Games' Soundtrack Song?|publisher=[[MTV]]|date=October 28, 2014|accessdate=November 18, 2014}}<br/>{{cite web|url=https://variancemagazine.com/news/4230-ariana-grande-reveals-hunger-games-collaboration-with-lorde-diplo|title=Ariana Grande Reveals 'Hunger Games' Collaboration with Lorde, Diplo|publisher=Variance Magazine|date=October 29, 2014|accessdate=November 18, 2014}}</ref> A week later, Grande revealed in a livestream that she was included in the film's soundtrack. She described the song as \"very interesting\" and \"very different.\"<ref name=\"MTVHungerGames\"/> Lorde announced the track's title via Twitter on 3 November 2014.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6304444/ariana-grande-major-lazer-lorde-hunger-games-mockingjay-soundtrack|title=Ariana Grande & Major Lazer Teaming Up for Lorde's 'Hunger Games: Mockingjay' Soundtrack|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=November 3, 2014|accessdate=November 18, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Composition and reception==\n\"All My Love\" is an [[electropop]] and [[dance-pop]] song,<ref name=\"Stereogum\"/> with elements of dancehall.<ref name=\"CoSreview\"/> ''[[Stereogum]]''{{'}}s Tom Breihan compared it to Grande's previous single, \"[[Break Free (Ariana Grande song)|Break Free]]\" (2014), featuring Russian-German DJ [[Zedd (musician)|Zedd]].<ref name=\"Stereogum\">{{cite news|last1=Breihan|first1=Tom|title=Major Lazer \u2013 \u201cAll My Love\u201d (Feat. Ariana Grande)|url=https://www.stereogum.com/1718551/major-lazer-all-my-love-feat-ariana-grande/mp3s/|accessdate=18 May 2018|work=Stereogum|date=13 November 2014}}</ref> Bradley Stern from ''[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]'' described its production as having \"rich, tribal\" sounds and \"\u201990\u2019s-leaning dance floor pulsations\".<ref name=\"idolator\">{{cite news |last1=Stern |first1=Bradley |title=Ariana Grande And Major Lazer\u2019s \u2018Hunger Games\u2019 Song, \u201cAll My Love\u201d: Listen |url=https://www.idolator.com/7570345/ariana-grande-major-lazer-hunger-games-song-all-my-love-listen |accessdate=30 August 2018 |work=Idolator |date=13 November 2014}}</ref> ''[[Exclaim!|Exclaim]]'' writer Alex Hudson called the track an \"electronic banger with in-your-face beats and a manic breakdown.\" Hudson said that the juxtaposition of the song's \"freaky beats\" with Grande's vocals build a \"rather tame pop foundation\".<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hudson|first1=Alex|title=Major Lazer \"All My Love\" (ft. Ariana Grande)|url=http://exclaim.ca/music/article/major_lazer-all_my_love_ft_ariana_grande|accessdate=18 May 2018|work=Exclaim!|date=13 November 2014}}</ref> Similarly, ''[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]'' writer Edwin Ortiz called the song an \"electronic pop cut\" with a \"heart-pulsing backdrop\".<ref name=\"complex\">{{cite news|last1=Ortiz|first1=Edwin|title=Listen to Major Lazer's \"All My Love\" f/ Ariana Grande|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2014/11/major-lazer-f-ariana-grande-all-my-love|accessdate=18 May 2018|work=Complex|date=13 November 2014}}</ref> Brennan Carley of ''[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]'' noted that the song features \"yelping, punctuated beats and synthesizers [that] pierce the air\".<ref name=\"spin\">{{cite news|last1=Carley|first1=Brennan|title=Major Lazer and Ariana Grande Team Up for Piercing \u2018Mockingjay\u2019 Cut|url=https://www.spin.com/2014/11/ariana-grande-major-lazer-mockingjay-all-my-love-stream/|accessdate=18 May 2018|work=Spin|date=13 November 2014}}</ref> Critics described Grande's vocals on the track as \"sweet\",<ref name=\"complex\"/> \"smooth\",<ref name=\"idolator\"/> and \"angelic\".<ref name=\"CoSreview\"/>\n\n\"All My Love\" received mostly positive reviews from [[music journalism|music critics]]. Michelle Geslani from ''[[Consequence of Sound]]'' called the song a \"Grade A electropop banger.\" Geslani also praised both artists, stating that \"Diplo\u2019s dancehall alter ego doles out breezy yet bouncy island rhythms while Grande\u2019s angelic croon soars high above the seas.\"<ref name=\"CoSreview\">{{cite news|last1=Geslani|first1=Michelle|title=Ariana Grande and Major Lazer team up on \u201cAll My Love\u201d \u2014 listen|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2014/11/ariana-grande-and-major-lazer-team-up-on-all-my-love-listen/|accessdate=18 May 2018|work=Consequence of Sound|date=13 November 2014}}</ref> In a review of the soundtrack, Nick Levine of ''[[NME]]'' stated that both artists sounded like they were \"holding a rave in the rainforest\".<ref>{{cite news|last1=Levine|first1=Nick|title=Various Artists \u2013 \u2018The Hunger Games: Mockingjay Part 1 OST\u2019|url=http://www.nme.com/reviews/album/reviews-various-artists-15807|accessdate=18 May 2018|work=NME|date=19 November 2014}}</ref> In a mixed review of the soundtrack, Jim Farber of ''[[New York Daily News]]'' called Grande's inclusion in the song a \"commercial move\", stating that her vocals proved \"too mainstream for an album meant to project something sinister.\"<ref>{{cite news|last1=Farber|first1=Jim|title='The Hunger Games: Mockingjay Part 1 -- Original Motion Picture Soundtrack,' music review|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/music/hunger-games-mockingjay-part-1-music-review-article-1.2008451|accessdate=18 May 2018|work=New York Daily News|date=13 November 2014}}</ref> \"All My Love\" was moderately successful in Belgium, where it peaked within the top 40 in both the Flanders and Wallonia chart components.<ref name=\"flanders\"/><ref name=\"wallonia\"/> It reached number 135 in France and number 194 in the United Kingdom.<ref name=\"france\"/><ref name=\"UKcharts\"/>\n\n==Remix==\n{{Infobox song\n| name     = All My Love (Remix)\n| cover    = All My Love (Remix) Artwork.jpg\n| alt      = An animated picture of a man with armor kneeling down on a pile of scraps on a yellow and black background.\n| caption  =\n| type     = remix single\n| artist   = [[Major Lazer]] featuring Ariana Grande and [[Machel Montano]]\n| album    = [[Peace Is the Mission]]\n| released = January 21, 2015\n| format   =\n| recorded =\n| studio   =\n| venue    =\n| genre    = {{hlist|[[Soca music|Soca]]|[[house music|house]]}}\n| length   = {{ubl|{{duration|m=3|s=49}}}}\n| label    = [[Mad Decent]]\n| writer   = {{hlist|[[Diplo|Thomas Pentz]]|[[Boaz van de Beatz|Boaz de Jong]]|[[Jr Blender|Philip Meckseper]]|Ella Yelich-O'Connor|Ariana Grande-Butera|Karen \u00d8rsted|[[Machel Montano]]|[[Skinny Fabulous|Gamal Doyle]]}}\n| producer = {{hlist|Diplo|Boaz van de Beatz|Jr Blender}}\n}}\n\nOn 21 January 2015, a remix version featuring vocals from Ariana Grande and soca singer [[Machel Montano]] was released.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Wass |first1=Mike |title=Ariana Grande And Major Lazer\u2019s \u201cAll My Love\u201d Gets A Soca Remix Featuring Machel Montano: Listen |url=https://www.idolator.com/7577812/ariana-grande-major-lazer-all-my-love-soca-remix-machel-montano |accessdate=31 August 2018 |work=Idolator |date=21 January 2015}}</ref> It appears as the ninth track on [[Major Lazer]]'s third studio album, ''[[Peace Is the Mission]]'' (2015). [[Diplo|Thomas Pentz]], a member of Major Lazer, co-wrote the song with producers Boaz de Jong, [[Jr Blender|Philip Meckseper]], [[Skinny Fabulous|Gamal Doyle]] and featured artist Machel Montano.<ref name=\"pitmlinernotes\">{{cite AV media notes|others=Major Lazer|title=Peace Is the Mission|year=2015|publisher=Mad Decent}}</ref>\n\nAccording to ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'' writer Claire Lobenfeld, the song features an interpolation of [[Aqua (band)|Aqua]]'s \"[[Lollipop (Candyman)]]\" (1997) and has a \"[[dancehall]]-inflected festival [[dubstep]]\".<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lobenfeld|first1=Claire|title=Major Lazer: Peace Is the Mission Album Review|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/20519-peace-is-the-mission/|accessdate=12 March 2018|work=Pitchfork|date=3 June 2015}}</ref> Matt Medved from ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' labelled it as \"[[soca music|soca]]/[[house music|house]] mash\".<ref>{{cite news|last1=Medved|first1=Matt|title=Diplo\u2019s Major Lazer Finds Its Footing In the World of Pop With 'Peace Is the Mission': Album Review|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/review/6590208/diplo-major-lazer-peace-is-the-mission-review|accessdate=12 March 2018|work=Billboard|date=5 June 2015}}</ref> ''[[Rolling Stone]]''{{'}}s Jon Dolan called the remix a \"weapons-grade sun splash\".<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dolan |first1=Jon |title=Peace Is the Mission |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-album-reviews/peace-is-the-mission-83125/ |accessdate=31 August 2018 |work=Rolling Stone |date=2 June 2015}}</ref> Commercially, the remix of the song charted at number 87 on the ''Billboard'' Canadian Hot 100 chart<ref name=\"canadaremix\"/> and peaked at number 15 on the US Dance/Electronic Songs chart at number 66;<ref name=\"bderemix\"/> it reached number 66 on the latter's year-end chart.<ref name=\"bderemixyear-end\"/>\n{{Clear}}\n\n==Credits and personnel==\n'''Recording and management'''\n* Recorded at [[Associated Independent Recording|Air Lyndhurst]] (London, United Kingdom)\n* Published by [[Because Music]], [[Mad Decent]] and [[Warner Music Group]] (WMG) {{small|(Remix)}}\n\n'''Personnel'''\n\nCredits adapted from the liner notes of ''The Hunger Games: Mockingjay, Part 1 (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack)'' and ''Peace Is the Mission''.<ref name=linernotes/><ref name=\"pitmlinernotes\"/> All personnel contributed to both the solo and remix versions, except where noted.\n{{Div col}}\n* [[Major Lazer]] \u2013 lead artist, production\n* [[Ariana Grande|Ariana Grande-Butera]] \u2013 [[guest appearance|guest vocals]], songwriting\n* [[M\u00d8 (singer)|Karen \u00d8rsted]] \u2013 songwriting\n* [[Lorde|Ella Yelich-O\u2019Connor]] \u2013 songwriting\n* [[Boaz van de Beatz]] \u2013 production \n* [[Jr Blender]] \u2013 production\n* [[Machel Montano]] \u2013 guest vocals, songwriting {{small|(Remix only)}}\n* [[Diplo|Thomas Pentz]] \u2013 songwriting {{small|(Remix only)}}\n* Philip Meckseper \u2013 songwriting {{small|(Remix only)}}\n* [[Skinny Fabulous|Gamal Doyle]] \u2013 songwriting {{small|(Remix only)}}\n{{Div col end}}\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"| Chart (2014\u201316) !! Peak<br>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders Tip|35|artist=Major Lazer feat. Ariana Grande|song=All My Love|rowheader=true|accessdate=January 17, 2015|refname=\"flanders\"}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Wallonia Tip|34|artist=Major Lazer feat. Ariana Grande|song=All My Love|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 14, 2016|refname=\"wallonia\"}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Canada|87|artist=Major Lazer|rowheader=true|accessdate=August 12, 2015|refname=\"canadaremix\"|note=Machel Montano remix}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|France|135|artist=Major Lazer feat. Ariana Grande|song=All My Love|rowheader=true|accessdate=January 31, 2015|refname=\"france\"}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Scotland|82|date=2014-11-23|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 27, 2019|refname=\"scot\"}}\n|-\n! scope=row|UK Singles ([[UK Singles Chart|Official Charts Company]])<ref name=\"UKcharts\">{{cite web|last=Zywietz|first=Tobias|url=http://www.zobbel.de/cluk/141129cluk.txt |title=CHART: CLUK Update 29.11.2014 (wk47)|publisher=Zobbel|accessdate=November 29, 2014}}</ref>\n| 194\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboarddanceelectronic|15|artist=Major Lazer|rowheader=true|accessdate=January 6, 2016|refname=\"bderemix\"|note=Machel Montano remix}}\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!Chart (2015)\n!Position\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|US Dance/Electronic Songs (''Billboard'')<ref name=\"bderemixyear-end\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2015/hot-dance-electronic--songs|title=2015 Year End Charts \u2013 Dance/Electronic Songs|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=January 9, 2016}}</ref><br/>{{small|''Machel Montano remix''}}\n| 66\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{MetroLyrics song|major-lazer|all-my-love}}\n*{{YouTube|O5wlxT9ygtY|\"All My Love\" (feat. Ariana Grande & Machel Montano) (Remix)}}\n\n{{Major Lazer|state=collapsed}}\n{{Ariana Grande songs|state=collapsed}}\n{{Navboxes|list1=\n{{Machel Montano}}\n{{The Hunger Games}}\n}}\n\n[[Category:2014 songs]]\n[[Category:Aqua (band)]]\n[[Category:Ariana Grande songs]]\n[[Category:Dancehall songs]]\n[[Category:Electropop songs]]\n[[Category:House music songs]]\n[[Category:Major Lazer songs]]\n[[Category:Soca songs]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Diplo]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Ariana Grande]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Lorde]]\n[[Category:Songs written by M\u00d8]]\n[[Category:The Hunger Games music]]\n", "text_old": "{{good article}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name     = All My Love\n| cover    = ML AG AML.jpg\n| alt      = An animated image of a man with armor kneeling down while surrounded in a pile of metal scraps. A yellow spotlight appears along a black and light pink background.\n| caption  = Artwork released by Major Lazer\n| type     = song\n| artist   = [[Major Lazer]] featuring [[Ariana Grande]]\n| album    = [[The Hunger Games: Mockingjay, Part 1 (soundtrack)|The Hunger Games:<br>Mockingjay, Part 1]]\n| released = {{Start date|2014|11|13|df=yes}}\n| format   = [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| recorded =\n| studio   =\n| venue    =\n| genre    = {{hlist|[[Dancehall]]|[[electropop]]}}\n| length   = {{Duration|m=3|s=32}}\n| label    = [[Republic Records|Republic]]\n| writer   = {{hlist|[[Lorde|Ella Yelich-O'Connor]]|[[Ariana Grande|Ariana Grande-Butera]]|[[M\u00d8|Karen \u00d8rsted]]|[[Diplo|Thomas Pentz]]|[[Boaz van de Beatz|Boaz de Jong]]|[[Jr Blender|Philip Meckseper]]}}\n| producer = {{hlist|[[Diplo]]|[[Boaz van de Beatz]]|[[Jr Blender]]}}\n| tracks   = {{The Hunger Games: Mockingjay, Part 1 track listing}}\n}}\n\n\"'''All My Love'''\" is a song by American electronic music project [[Major Lazer]] featuring vocals from American singer [[Ariana Grande]]. It was released on 13 November 2014 as the fifth song from the [[The Hunger Games: Mockingjay, Part 1 (soundtrack)|soundtrack]] for ''[[The Hunger Games: Mockingjay, Part 1]]'' (2014) by [[Republic Records]]. The song was written by Grande, [[Lorde|Ella Yelich-O'Connor]], and [[M\u00d8|Karen \u00d8rsted]] with production handled by [[Boaz van de Beatz]], Jr Blender and [[Diplo]], a member of Major Lazer. It is an [[electropop]] song with elements of [[dancehall]]. It received positive reviews from [[music journalism|music critics]] who complimented the track's production.\n\nCommercially, the track performed modestly in Belgium and charted in France and the United Kingdom. A remix of the song featuring vocals from Grande and soca singer [[Machel Montano]] was released on 21 January 2015 and appears as the final track on Major Lazer's third studio album ''[[Peace Is the Mission]]'' (2015). It features an interpolation of [[Aqua (band)|Aqua]]'s 1997 song \"[[Lollipop (Candyman)]]\". This version performed modestly in Belgium and charted in Canada, peaking at 15 and 87, respectively.\n\n==Background and release==\n[[File:Dangerous Woman Tour in Manchester4 (cropped).jpg|left|thumb|upright|alt=An zoomed-in image of a woman dressed in a white crop top, pants and a jacket performing on stage.|[[Ariana Grande]] co-wrote and contributed vocals to \"All My Love\"]]\n\"All My Love\" was written by [[Lorde]] (credited under her birth-name Ella Yelich-O'Connor), [[Ariana Grande]] and [[M\u00d8|Karen \u00d8rsted]],<ref name=linernotes>{{cite AV media notes|others=Lorde|title=The Hunger Games: Mockingjay \u2013 Part 1|year=2014|publisher=Republic Records}}</ref> while production of the song was handled by Boaz van de Beatz, Jr Blender and [[Diplo]], a member of [[Major Lazer]]. Leaked on 13 November 2014 before the official release date,<ref name=\"spin\"/> \"All My Love\" was included as the fifth track for the [[The Hunger Games: Mockingjay, Part 1 (soundtrack)|soundtrack album]] of the 2014 film ''[[The Hunger Games: Mockingjay \u2013 Part 1|The Hunger Games: Mockingjay, Part 1]]''.<ref name=linernotes/>\n\nLorde's desire to include \"All My Love\" on the film's soundtrack led Diplo to rush the production process of the song. In an annotation posted to [[Genius (website)|Genius]] that Diplo wrote, he mentioned that he was on vacation in London at the same time Grande was there. He managed to communicate with her and go \"back and forth with certain mixes.\" Diplo said that he was willing to \"screw around\" and surprise people with \"this kind of collaboration.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Major Lazer \u2014 All My Love Lyrics|url=https://genius.com/8506300|website=Genius|accessdate=18 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nDiplo first mentioned the track on 16 October 2014 via [[Twitter]]. However, he deleted the tweet afterwards.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Wass |first1=Mike |title=Diplo Reveals Looming Ariana Grande And Major Lazer Collaboration, Possibly Called \u201cAll My Love\u201d |url=http://www.idolator.com/7566836/ariana-grande-diplo-major-lazer-all-my-love-collaboration |accessdate=30 August 2018 |work=Idolator |date=16 October 2014}}</ref> When the album's official track list was announced on 21 October 2014, the song was listed as \"Track 5\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1970037/kanye-haim-pusha-t-charlie-xcx-mockingjay-soundtrack/|title=Lorde's 'Mockingjay' Soundtrack Features Kanye, Haim, Pusha T And Charli XCX|publisher=[[MTV]]|date=October 21, 2014|accessdate=November 18, 2014}}</ref> Lorde, who curated the film's soundtrack, said on Twitter that the song was not excluded for \"secrecy's sake\" but because it was \"not quite finished\".<ref name=\"MTVHungerGames\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1979171/ariana-grande-hunger-games-mockingjay-soundtrack/|title=Is Ariana Grande Behind That Secret 'Hunger Games' Soundtrack Song?|publisher=[[MTV]]|date=October 28, 2014|accessdate=November 18, 2014}}<br/>{{cite web|url=https://variancemagazine.com/news/4230-ariana-grande-reveals-hunger-games-collaboration-with-lorde-diplo|title=Ariana Grande Reveals 'Hunger Games' Collaboration with Lorde, Diplo|publisher=Variance Magazine|date=October 29, 2014|accessdate=November 18, 2014}}</ref> A week later, Grande revealed in a livestream that she was included in the film's soundtrack. She described the song as \"very interesting\" and \"very different.\"<ref name=\"MTVHungerGames\"/> Lorde announced the track's title via Twitter on 3 November 2014.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6304444/ariana-grande-major-lazer-lorde-hunger-games-mockingjay-soundtrack|title=Ariana Grande & Major Lazer Teaming Up for Lorde's 'Hunger Games: Mockingjay' Soundtrack|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=November 3, 2014|accessdate=November 18, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Composition and reception==\n\"All My Love\" is an [[electropop]] and [[dance-pop]] song,<ref name=\"Stereogum\"/> with elements of dancehall.<ref name=\"CoSreview\"/> ''[[Stereogum]]''{{'}}s Tom Breihan compared it to Grande's previous single, \"[[Break Free (Ariana Grande song)|Break Free]]\" (2014), featuring Russian-German DJ [[Zedd (musician)|Zedd]].<ref name=\"Stereogum\">{{cite news|last1=Breihan|first1=Tom|title=Major Lazer \u2013 \u201cAll My Love\u201d (Feat. Ariana Grande)|url=https://www.stereogum.com/1718551/major-lazer-all-my-love-feat-ariana-grande/mp3s/|accessdate=18 May 2018|work=Stereogum|date=13 November 2014}}</ref> Bradley Stern from ''[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]'' described its production as having \"rich, tribal\" sounds and \"\u201990\u2019s-leaning dance floor pulsations\".<ref name=\"idolator\">{{cite news |last1=Stern |first1=Bradley |title=Ariana Grande And Major Lazer\u2019s \u2018Hunger Games\u2019 Song, \u201cAll My Love\u201d: Listen |url=https://www.idolator.com/7570345/ariana-grande-major-lazer-hunger-games-song-all-my-love-listen |accessdate=30 August 2018 |work=Idolator |date=13 November 2014}}</ref> ''[[Exclaim!|Exclaim]]'' writer Alex Hudson called the track an \"electronic banger with in-your-face beats and a manic breakdown.\" Hudson said that the juxtaposition of the song's \"freaky beats\" with Grande's vocals build a \"rather tame pop foundation\".<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hudson|first1=Alex|title=Major Lazer \"All My Love\" (ft. Ariana Grande)|url=http://exclaim.ca/music/article/major_lazer-all_my_love_ft_ariana_grande|accessdate=18 May 2018|work=Exclaim!|date=13 November 2014}}</ref> Similarly, ''[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]'' writer Edwin Ortiz called the song an \"electronic pop cut\" with a \"heart-pulsing backdrop\".<ref name=\"complex\">{{cite news|last1=Ortiz|first1=Edwin|title=Listen to Major Lazer's \"All My Love\" f/ Ariana Grande|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2014/11/major-lazer-f-ariana-grande-all-my-love|accessdate=18 May 2018|work=Complex|date=13 November 2014}}</ref> Brennan Carley of ''[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]'' noted that the song features \"yelping, punctuated beats and synthesizers [that] pierce the air\".<ref name=\"spin\">{{cite news|last1=Carley|first1=Brennan|title=Major Lazer and Ariana Grande Team Up for Piercing \u2018Mockingjay\u2019 Cut|url=https://www.spin.com/2014/11/ariana-grande-major-lazer-mockingjay-all-my-love-stream/|accessdate=18 May 2018|work=Spin|date=13 November 2014}}</ref> Critics described Grande's vocals on the track as \"sweet\",<ref name=\"complex\"/> \"smooth\",<ref name=\"idolator\"/> and \"angelic\".<ref name=\"CoSreview\"/>\n\n\"All My Love\" received mostly positive reviews from [[music journalism|music critics]]. Michelle Geslani from ''[[Consequence of Sound]]'' called the song a \"Grade A electropop banger.\" Geslani also praised both artists, stating that \"Diplo\u2019s dancehall alter ego doles out breezy yet bouncy island rhythms while Grande\u2019s angelic croon soars high above the seas.\"<ref name=\"CoSreview\">{{cite news|last1=Geslani|first1=Michelle|title=Ariana Grande and Major Lazer team up on \u201cAll My Love\u201d \u2014 listen|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2014/11/ariana-grande-and-major-lazer-team-up-on-all-my-love-listen/|accessdate=18 May 2018|work=Consequence of Sound|date=13 November 2014}}</ref> In a review of the soundtrack, Nick Levine of ''[[NME]]'' stated that both artists sounded like they were \"holding a rave in the rainforest\".<ref>{{cite news|last1=Levine|first1=Nick|title=Various Artists \u2013 \u2018The Hunger Games: Mockingjay Part 1 OST\u2019|url=http://www.nme.com/reviews/album/reviews-various-artists-15807|accessdate=18 May 2018|work=NME|date=19 November 2014}}</ref> In a mixed review of the soundtrack, Jim Farber of ''[[New York Daily News]]'' called Grande's inclusion in the song a \"commercial move\", stating that her vocals proved \"too mainstream for an album meant to project something sinister.\"<ref>{{cite news|last1=Farber|first1=Jim|title='The Hunger Games: Mockingjay Part 1 -- Original Motion Picture Soundtrack,' music review|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/music/hunger-games-mockingjay-part-1-music-review-article-1.2008451|accessdate=18 May 2018|work=New York Daily News|date=13 November 2014}}</ref> \"All My Love\" was moderately successful in Belgium, where it peaked within the top 40 in both the Flanders and Wallonia chart components.<ref name=\"flanders\"/><ref name=\"wallonia\"/> It reached number 135 in France and number 194 in the United Kingdom.<ref name=\"france\"/><ref name=\"UKcharts\"/>\n\n==Remix==\n{{Infobox song\n| name     = All My Love (Remix)\n| cover    = All My Love (Remix) Artwork.jpg\n| alt      = An animated picture of a man with armor kneeling down on a pile of scraps on a yellow and black background.\n| caption  =\n| type     = remix single\n| artist   = [[Major Lazer]] featuring Ariana Grande and [[Machel Montano]]\n| album    = [[Peace Is the Mission]]\n| released = {{start date|2015|01|21|df=y}}\n| format   =\n| recorded =\n| studio   =\n| venue    =\n| genre    = {{hlist|[[Soca music|Soca]]|[[house music|house]]}}\n| length   = {{ubl|{{duration|m=3|s=49}}}}\n| label    = [[Mad Decent]]\n| writer   = {{hlist|[[Diplo|Thomas Pentz]]|[[Boaz van de Beatz|Boaz de Jong]]|[[Jr Blender|Philip Meckseper]]|Ella Yelich-O'Connor|Ariana Grande-Butera|Karen \u00d8rsted|[[Machel Montano]]|[[Skinny Fabulous|Gamal Doyle]]}}\n| producer = {{hlist|Diplo|Boaz van de Beatz|Jr Blender}}\n}}\n\nOn 21 January 2015, a remix version featuring vocals from Ariana Grande and soca singer [[Machel Montano]] was released.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Wass |first1=Mike |title=Ariana Grande And Major Lazer\u2019s \u201cAll My Love\u201d Gets A Soca Remix Featuring Machel Montano: Listen |url=https://www.idolator.com/7577812/ariana-grande-major-lazer-all-my-love-soca-remix-machel-montano |accessdate=31 August 2018 |work=Idolator |date=21 January 2015}}</ref> It appears as the ninth track on [[Major Lazer]]'s third studio album, ''[[Peace Is the Mission]]'' (2015). [[Diplo|Thomas Pentz]], a member of Major Lazer, co-wrote the song with producers Boaz de Jong, [[Jr Blender|Philip Meckseper]], [[Skinny Fabulous|Gamal Doyle]] and featured artist Machel Montano.<ref name=\"pitmlinernotes\">{{cite AV media notes|others=Major Lazer|title=Peace Is the Mission|year=2015|publisher=Mad Decent}}</ref>\n\nAccording to ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'' writer Claire Lobenfeld, the song features an interpolation of [[Aqua (band)|Aqua]]'s \"[[Lollipop (Candyman)]]\" (1997) and has a \"[[dancehall]]-inflected festival [[dubstep]]\".<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lobenfeld|first1=Claire|title=Major Lazer: Peace Is the Mission Album Review|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/20519-peace-is-the-mission/|accessdate=12 March 2018|work=Pitchfork|date=3 June 2015}}</ref> Matt Medved from ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' labelled it as \"[[soca music|soca]]/[[house music|house]] mash\".<ref>{{cite news|last1=Medved|first1=Matt|title=Diplo\u2019s Major Lazer Finds Its Footing In the World of Pop With 'Peace Is the Mission': Album Review|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/review/6590208/diplo-major-lazer-peace-is-the-mission-review|accessdate=12 March 2018|work=Billboard|date=5 June 2015}}</ref> ''[[Rolling Stone]]''{{'}}s Jon Dolan called the remix a \"weapons-grade sun splash\".<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dolan |first1=Jon |title=Peace Is the Mission |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-album-reviews/peace-is-the-mission-83125/ |accessdate=31 August 2018 |work=Rolling Stone |date=2 June 2015}}</ref> Commercially, the remix of the song charted at number 87 on the ''Billboard'' Canadian Hot 100 chart<ref name=\"canadaremix\"/> and peaked at number 15 on the US Dance/Electronic Songs chart at number 66;<ref name=\"bderemix\"/> it reached number 66 on the latter's year-end chart.<ref name=\"bderemixyear-end\"/>\n{{Clear}}\n\n==Credits and personnel==\n'''Recording and management'''\n* Recorded at [[Associated Independent Recording|Air Lyndhurst]] (London, United Kingdom)\n* Published by [[Because Music]], [[Mad Decent]] and [[Warner Music Group]] (WMG) {{small|(Remix)}}\n\n'''Personnel'''\n\nCredits adapted from the liner notes of ''The Hunger Games: Mockingjay, Part 1 (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack)'' and ''Peace Is the Mission''.<ref name=linernotes/><ref name=\"pitmlinernotes\"/> All personnel contributed to both the solo and remix versions, except where noted.\n{{Div col}}\n* [[Major Lazer]] \u2013 lead artist, production\n* [[Ariana Grande|Ariana Grande-Butera]] \u2013 [[guest appearance|guest vocals]], songwriting\n* [[M\u00d8 (singer)|Karen \u00d8rsted]] \u2013 songwriting\n* [[Lorde|Ella Yelich-O\u2019Connor]] \u2013 songwriting\n* [[Boaz van de Beatz]] \u2013 production \n* [[Jr Blender]] \u2013 production\n* [[Machel Montano]] \u2013 guest vocals, songwriting {{small|(Remix only)}}\n* [[Diplo|Thomas Pentz]] \u2013 songwriting {{small|(Remix only)}}\n* Philip Meckseper \u2013 songwriting {{small|(Remix only)}}\n* [[Skinny Fabulous|Gamal Doyle]] \u2013 songwriting {{small|(Remix only)}}\n{{Div col end}}\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"| Chart (2014\u201316) !! Peak<br>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders Tip|35|artist=Major Lazer feat. Ariana Grande|song=All My Love|rowheader=true|accessdate=January 17, 2015|refname=\"flanders\"}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Wallonia Tip|34|artist=Major Lazer feat. Ariana Grande|song=All My Love|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 14, 2016|refname=\"wallonia\"}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Canada