 and was later included in his second EP ''[[Cyan (EP)|Cyan]]'' on March 24, 2020. The digital single included a second track \"Adulthood\", which was co-written by Kang.\n\n== Background ==\nOn November 13, 2019, Kang Daniel posted a surprise teaser image on social media and announced news of a digital single release on the 25th at 6pm KST, marking his first comeback after releasing ''[[Color on Me]]'' four months prior.<ref>{{cite news|title=\uac15\ub2e4\ub2c8\uc5d8, 25\uc77c \uc2f1\uae00 \ubc1c\ub9e4..4\uac1c\uc6d4\ub9cc \uae30\uc2b5 \ucef4\ubc31(\uacf5\uc2dd) \ubcf8\ubb38\ub4e3\uae30 \uc124\uc815|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/108/0002823352|work=Star News|date=November 13, 2019|access-date=April 15, 2020|language=ko}}</ref> The first set of black and white [[Film noir|noir]]-themed concept photos was posted on the 20th, and a second set of photos featuring Kang in a burgundy suit was posted on the 21st.<ref>{{cite news|title=\ub204\uc544\ub974 \uc8fc\uc778\uacf5 \ub41c \uac15\ub2e4\ub2c8\uc5d8?\u2026\uc2e0\ubcf4 TOUCHIN' \ucf58\uc149\ud2b8 \ud3ec\ud1a0 \uccab \uacf5\uac1c\n|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=416&aid=0000251607|work=SBS funE|date=November 20, 2019|access-date=April 15, 2020|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=\ubc84\uac74\ub514 \uc288\ud2b8 \uc7a5\ucc29\ud55c \uac15\ub2e4\ub2c8\uc5d8\u2026TOUCHIN' \ub450 \ubc88\uc9f8 \ucf58\uc149\ud2b8 \ud3ec\ud1a0|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=416&aid=0000251660|work=SBS funE|date=November 21, 2019|access-date=April 15, 2020|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n== Composition ==\n\"Touchin'\" is described as an '80s-'90s pop sound tied together with EDM, rock, and dance genres with a strong bass in the chorus. The song is an interpretation of a magnetic first meeting between a film's two main characters as the motif.\n\n\u201cAdulthood\u201d is about becoming an adult but also not wanting to yet. Lyrically, there is push and pull between the ideal adult self with a free soul and the tired and lonely adult self in reality. The song has a lively melody and features a soft synthesizer.<ref>{{cite news|title=\ub354 \ub113\uc5b4\uc9c4 \uac15\ub2e4\ub2c8\uc5d8\uc758 \uc74c\uc545\uc801 \uc2a4\ud399\ud2b8\ub7fc\u2026\ud0c0\uc774\ud2c0\uace1\uc740 \"TOUCHIN'\"|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/311/0001076052|work=Xports News|date=November 18, 2019|access-date=April 15, 2020|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n== Promotion ==\nKang debuted \"Touchin'\" at his ''Color on Seoul'' fan meeting held at [[Korea International Exhibition Center|KINTEX]] on November 23\u201324, 2019 prior to the official music site release.<ref>{{cite news|title=\ub354 \ub113\uc5b4\uc9c4 \uac15\ub2e4\ub2c8\uc5d8\uc758 \uc74c\uc545\uc801 \uc2a4\ud399\ud2b8\ub7fc\u2026\ud0c0\uc774\ud2c0\uace1\uc740 \"TOUCHIN'\"|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/311/0001076052|work=Xports News|date=November 18, 2019|access-date=April 15, 2020|language=ko}}</ref> Kang performed \"Touchin'\" at awards shows [[Asia Artist Awards]] on November 26 and the [[2019 Melon Music Awards]]. He also made radio and variety appearances, guesting on ''[[Cultwo Show]]'' and becoming a special MC for ''[[Happy Together (talk show)|Happy Together]]'', where his segment resulted in the highest one-minute viewership. His [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]]'s ''Entertainment Weekly'' interview aired as part of the show's final episode.<ref>{{cite news|title=\uac15\ub2e4\ub2c8\uc5d8 '\ud130\uce6d' \ucef4\ubc31 1\uc8fc\ucc28 #\uc131\uacf5\uc801 #\ucd5c\uace0\uc7581\ubd84 #4\uad00\uc655|url=https://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=106&oid=108&aid=0002827430|work=Star News|date=December 2, 2019|access-date=April 15, 2020}}</ref> He was able to promote on music shows [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS2]]'s ''[[Music Bank (TV series)|Music Bank]]'', [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]]' ''[[Inkigayo]]'', and [[SBS MTV]]'s ''[[The Show (South Korean TV series)|The Show]]''. His return to music shows spanned nearly a year since his last music show performance in December 2018, and he received a music show award in person on ''[[The Show (South Korean TV series)|The Show]]'' on December 3, 2019.<ref>{{cite news|title=\uc57d 1\ub144 \ub9cc\uc5d0 \uc5c5\ub370\uc774\ud2b8 \ub41c \uac15\ub2e4\ub2c8\uc5d8 \u2018\ubba4\uc9c1\ubc45\ud06c\u2019 \ubb34\ub300 \uc601\uc0c1|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=311&aid=0001081324|work=Xports News|date=November 30, 2019|access-date=April 15, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title='\uc778\uae30\uac00\uc694' \uac15\ub2e4\ub2c8\uc5d8, \ud55c \ud3b8 \uc601\ud654 \uac19\uc740 \ube44\uc8fc\uc5bc..\ub3c5\ubcf4\uc801 \uc874\uc7ac\uac10 'TOUCHIN'|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=112&aid=0003241921|work=Herald Pop|date=December 1, 2019|access-date=April 15, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title='\ub354\uc1fc' \uac15\ub2e4\ub2c8\uc5d8, \ucef4\ubc31 \ud6c4 \uccab 1\uc704\u2026\ubd95\uc5b4\ube75 \uba39\ubc29 \uacf5\uc57d \uc9c0\ucf30\ub2e4 [\uc885\ud569]|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=311&aid=0001082729|work=Xports News|date=December 1, 2019|access-date=April 15, 2020}}</ref> After Kang promoted for a week, Konnect announced he would be taking a break due to health issues.<ref>{{cite news|title=#WeAreWithDaniel Trends As K-pop Star Kang Daniel Takes Career Break Due To Health Issues|url=https://www.newsweek.com/k-pop-kang-daniel-break-mental-health-depression-anxiety-panic-disorder-1475453|work=Newsweek|date=December 4, 2019|access-date=April 15, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Music video ==\nThe \"Touchin'\" music video teaser was revealed on November 22, 2019, and the full music video produced by FantazyLab was released on November 25, 2019. The video features Kang in a casual setting watching a black and white film on an old CRT TV.<ref>{{cite news|title=\uac15\ub2e4\ub2c8\uc5d8, \uc2e0\uace1 'TOUCHIN' \ud2f0\uc800\u2025\ube14\ub85d\ubc84\uc2a4\ud130\uae09 \uc2a4\ucf00\uc77c \uc601\ud654\uac19\uc740 \ubd84\uc704\uae30\n|url=https://enterta